The directory pdb_crd contains the atomic coordinates of all PDB files used by 3V software to find the volume and surface area of all PDB structures.
The directory res_crd_bf contains the atomic coordinates of all PDB files and the corresponding B factors, that are representative of individual sites in proteins. The atoms considered are: N,CA,C,O,CB,SC,AA with SC standing for side chain and AA standing for Amino Acid.

